-- Sun Pharma Buys Templeton Taro Stake for $82 Million, Standard Reports
-- B y   T h o m a s   A b r a h a m
-- 2010-11-12T01:44:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-12/sun-pharma-buys-templeton-taro-stake-for-82-million-standard-reports.html
Sun Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd.,
India’s biggest drugmaker by market value, bought a 12 percent
stake in Taro Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd. from Templeton
Asset Management for $82 million, the Business Standard
reported, without saying where it got the information. Sun paid
$16 per share to buy Templeton’s stake, raising the Indian
company’s holding to 65.2 percent, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
